"{\n    \"Title\": \"Notes to the Consolidated Financial StatementsFor the year ended March 31, 2020\",\n    \"row 1\": \"1. Operations\",\n    \"row 2\": \"The Niisaachewan Anishinaabe Nation (the \\\"Nation\\\") is located in the Province of Ontario, and provides various services to\",\n    \"row 3\": \"its members.\",\n    \"row 4\": \"2. Significant accounting policies\",\n    \"row 5\": \"These consolidated financial statements are the representations of management, prepared in accordance with Canadian\",\n    \"row 6\": \"public sector accounting principles and include the following significant accounting policies:\",\n    \"row 7\": \"Cash\",\n    \"row 8\": \"Cash includes balances with chartered banks.\",\n    \"row 9\": \"Funds held in Ottawa Trust Fund\",\n    \"row 10\": \"The funds held in trust in the consolidated revenue fund of the Government of Canada are subject to audit by the office of\",\n    \"row 11\": \"the Auditor General of Canada. Revenue from the funds held in trust are recognized in the year in which it is earned when it\",\n    \"row 12\": \"is measurable and collection is reasonably assured. Trust monies consist of:\",\n    \"row 13\": \"e Capital trust monies derived from non-renewable resource transactions on the sale of land or other Nation capital\",\n    \"row 14\": \"assets; and\",\n    \"row 15\": \"e Revenue trust monies generated primarily through land leasing transactions or interest earned on deposits held in\",\n    \"row 16\": \"trust.\",\n    \"row 17\": \"Portfolio investments\",\n    \"row 18\": \"Portfolio investments not quoted in an active market are recorded at amortized cost. Portfolio investments are written down\",\n    \"row 19\": \"where there has been a loss in value that is other than a temporary decline.\",\n    \"row 20\": \"Tangible capital assets\",\n    \"row 21\": \"Tangible capital assets are initially recorded at cost based on historical cost accounting records. Contributed tangible capital\",\n    \"row 22\": \"assets are recorded at their fair value at the date of contribution.\",\n    \"row 23\": \"Amortization\",\n    \"row 24\": \"Tangible capital assets are amortized annually using the straight line method at rates intended to amortize the cost of the\",\n    \"row 25\": \"assets over their estimated useful lives:\",\n    \"row 26\": \"Method Rate\",\n    \"row 27\": \"Water and Sewer - Infrastructure straight-line 40 years\",\n    \"row 28\": \"Water and Sewer - Buildings straight-line 30 years\",\n    \"row 29\": \"Electrical Systems straight-line 20 years\",\n    \"row 30\": \"Roads straight-line 40 years\",\n    \"row 31\": \"Office Furniture and Equipment straight-line 5 years\",\n    \"row 32\": \"Heavy Equipment straight-line 10 years\",\n    \"row 33\": \"Automotive straight-line 5-10 years\",\n    \"row 34\": \"Machinery and Equipment straight-line 5 years\",\n    \"row 35\": \"Community Buildings straight-line 30 years\",\n    \"row 36\": \"Band Housing straight-line 40 years\",\n    \"row 37\": \"CMHC Housing straight-line 40 years\",\n    \"row 38\": \"During the year assets under construction with a carrying value of $2,349,072 were put into use. Amortization has been\",\n    \"row 39\": \"recorded for the current year.\"\n}"